<title>CANADA: Canadian tax cut only a fraction of total book tax.</title>
<headline>Canadian tax cut only a fraction of total book tax.</headline>
<dateline>OTTAWA 1996-10-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The tax cut on some book sales announced by Finance Minister Paul Martin on Wednesday amounts to a fraction of the total tax on books across Canada, a Finance Department official said.</p>
<p>Martin announced that the government intended to eliminate the seven percent goods and services tax (GST) on books for schools, libraries, universities and certain charities and other front-line literacy groups.</p>
<p>The Finance official, responding to a query, said that was worth about C$25 million, out of a total GST of C$140 million collected on books.</p>
<p>Altogether, the federal government collects approximately C$345 million on books, magazines and newspapers, he added.</p>
<p>-- Randall Palmer, Reuters Ottawa Bureau 613-235-6745</p>
